@startuml
hide empty members
abstract class Alpha<<PolicyCmptType>> { 
  +status: String
  ~derivedValue: Integer
  #computedAmount: Decimal
  -TYPE_CODE: String
}
note left of Alpha
Alpha is the abstract base class of
the policy hierarchy. It defines
the basic attributes and the link
to the product component.
end note
note right of Alpha::status
The current status of the policy.
end note
note right of Alpha::derivedValue
A derived value.
end note
note right of Alpha::computedAmount
A computed amount.
end note
note right of Alpha::TYPE_CODE
Constant for type identification.
end note
Alpha *-- Beta
Delta <-- Alpha
class Beta<<(V,lightSteelBlue)PolicyCmptType>> { 
  +statusKind: data.Status
  +unknownRef: data.UnknownEnum
}
note left of Beta
Beta is the concrete subclass of
Alpha.
end note
note right of Beta::statusKind
The kind of status, references enum data.Status.
end note
note right of Beta::unknownRef
References an enum that is not present in the model.
end note
Alpha <|-- Beta
class Delta<<(V,lightSteelBlue)PolicyCmptType>> { 
  +coverageId: String
}
note left of Delta
Delta is a policy from the coverage
package.
end note
note right of Delta::coverageId
Coverage identifier.
end note
@enduml